dence. As crises around the globe lead to reconsiderations of the place of capitalism, Beck's excavation of this little-known strand of Hayek's thought-and its failure-is timely and instructive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aCapitalism. 0aFree enterprise. 4aCharles Darwin. 4aF. A. Hayek. 4acapitalism. 4acultural evolution. 4aevolution. 4afree market. 4agroup selection. 4aliberalism. 4amorality. 4aprogress. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226556147423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226556147.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles